 se~ later what to do next b"his last name is kagramanov. the head doctor's name is izyat jamalogli" b'sadukhov.' b'' b'the "ambulance" arrived and i went home and got igor. they admitted him as a' b'patient, they gave us a private room, an isolation room. we stayed in the' b'hospital until the 4th.' b'' b'some police car came and they said, "emma, let\'s go." and the women, our' b'colleagues, then they saw the police car, became anxious and said, "where are' b'you taking her?" i say, "they\'re going to kill me, too and the' b'investigator says, "why are you saying that, we\'re going to make a positive' b'identification." we went to baku and they took me into the morgue i' b'still can\'t remember what hospital it was the investigator says, "let\'s' b'go, we need to be certain, maybe it\'s not shagen." and when i saw the caskets,' b'lying on top of one another, i went out of my mind. i say, "i can\'t look, no."' b'the investigator says, "are there any identifying marks?" i say, "let me see' b'the clothes, or the shoes, or even a sock, i\'ll recognize them." he says,' b'"isn\'t they\'re anything on his body?" i say he has seven gold teeth and his' b'finger, he only has half of one of his fingers. shagen was a carpenter, he had' b'been injured at work b'' b'they brought one of the sleeves of the shirt and sweater he was wearing, they' b'brought them and they were all burned when i saw them i shouted, "oh,' b'they burned him!" i shouted, i don\'t know, i fell down or maybe i sat' b'down, i don\'t remember. and that investigator says, "well fine, fine, since' b"we've identified that these are his clothes, and since his teeth since" b'he has seven gold teeth b'' b'on the 4th they told me: "emma, it\'s time to bury shagen now." i cried, "how,' b"how can i bury shagen when i have only one son and he's sick? i should inform" b'his relatives, he has three sisters, i can\'t do it by myself." they say, "ok,' b'you know the situation. how will they get here from karabagh? how wi